# Clerk Billing — Subscriptions, Plans & Feature Access

All subscription and payment logic in this project is handled by **Clerk Billing**. Never use Stripe directly, never roll custom billing logic, and never trust client-supplied plan or feature data.

## Available Plans

The following plan slugs are defined in the Clerk Dashboard and must be used exactly as shown:

| Slug | Description |
|---|---|
| `free_user` | Default free tier |
| `pro` | Paid pro tier |

## Available Features

The following feature slugs are defined in the Clerk Dashboard:

| Slug | Description |
|---|---|
| `3_deck_limit` | User is limited to 3 decks (free tier) |
| `unlimited_decks` | User can create unlimited decks (pro) |
| `ai_flashcard_generation` | User can generate flashcards with AI (pro) |

## Checking Access — Server Side with `has()`

Use the `has()` helper from the Clerk `auth()` object in Server Components and Server Actions. **Never** check plans or features on the client side for access control decisions.

```ts
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server"

// Check by plan
const { has } = await auth()
const isProUser = has({ plan: "pro" })

// Check by feature
const canUseAI = has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" })
const hasUnlimitedDecks = has({ feature: "unlimited_decks" })
```

### Example: Gate a Server Action by plan

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — Server Action checks plan before proceeding
"use server"
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server"

export async function generateAIFlashcards(deckId: number) {
  const { has } = await auth()
  if (!has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" })) {
    throw new Error("AI flashcard generation requires a Pro plan.")
  }
  // ... generation logic
}
```

### Example: Gate a Server Action by deck count (free tier limit)

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — enforce 3-deck limit for free users
"use server"
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server"
import { getDecksForUser } from "@/db/queries/decks"

export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const { userId, has } = await auth()
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized")

  const hasFreeLimit = has({ feature: "3_deck_limit" })
  if (hasFreeLimit) {
    const existing = await getDecksForUser(userId)
    if (existing.length >= 3) {
      throw new Error("Free plan is limited to 3 decks. Upgrade to Pro for unlimited decks.")
    }
  }

  // ... create deck
}
```

## Checking Access — Client Side with `<Show>`

Use the `<Show>` component from `@clerk/nextjs` to conditionally render UI elements. This is safe for **UI-only** gating (hiding buttons, banners, etc.) but must never be the sole access control — always enforce on the server too.

```tsx
import { Show } from "@clerk/nextjs"

// Show upgrade prompt to free users
<Show
  when={{ plan: "pro" }}
  fallback={<p>Upgrade to Pro to unlock unlimited decks.</p>}
>
  <CreateDeckButton />
</Show>

// Show AI generation button only to users with the feature
<Show
  when={{ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" }}
  fallback={<p>AI generation is a Pro feature.</p>}
>
  <GenerateWithAIButton />
</Show>
```

## Pricing Page

Use the `<PricingTable />` component from `@clerk/nextjs` to display plans. Place it on a dedicated `/pricing` page.

```tsx
// app/pricing/page.tsx
import { PricingTable } from "@clerk/nextjs"

export default function PricingPage() {
  return (
    <div style={{ maxWidth: "800px", margin: "0 auto", padding: "0 1rem" }}>
      <PricingTable />
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Rules Summary

- **Always** use `has({ plan: "..." })` or `has({ feature: "..." })` — never hardcode plan logic.
- **Always** enforce billing checks on the **server** (Server Components or Server Actions) for any real access control.
- **Never** use `<Show>` as the only gate for protected functionality — it is UI-only.
- **Never** accept plan or feature information as input from the client.
- **Never** use Stripe APIs directly — all billing flows go through Clerk.
- **Always** use the exact plan and feature slugs listed above.
